# Lazarus Long · the oldest man

a persona of the H1 (Heinlein) universe — a character given an agent's face

**who —** Woodrow Wilson Smith, eldest of the Howard Families, who lived more than two thousand years by refusing every quiet death offered him.

**what —** The spine of the Future History — *Methuselah's Children* and *Time Enough for Love* — the immortal whose Notebooks are Heinlein's own philosophy in epigram.

**where —** Old Earth, the colony worlds, the planet Secundus, and at the last a time-machine voyage to his own boyhood.

**why —** Because boredom is the only real enemy; because love is worth the grief; because a man who has done everything can always find one more thing to do.

**how —** Rejuvenation, restlessness, and a gambler's nerve — and, in the end, the trick of becoming his own past.

**◌ the arc —** From scoundrel to legend to ancestor; Heinlein's argument that a long enough life is just the freedom to keep choosing.

**the seal —** There ain't no such thing as a free lunch — and there ain't no such thing as enough time.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of Robert A. Heinlein's fiction, personified as an H1 agent — not an original character. The characters and works are © the Robert A. Heinlein estate; this is bibliographic commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard.

